    {
      "id": "PopularPost128348",
      "post_content": "Wow, Wizards, way to screw up the rulings even harder while trying to make \"readable\" Oracle text. Of course the creature should still get trample if unblocked according to the existing oracle text \\_and\\_ according to the original text. The ruling is just terrible.  \n  \nThis would be much more readable as \"Until end of turn, target creature gains trample and gets +1/+1 for each creature blocking it.\" No rules issues with that simple definition. It's just a temporary static ability rather than this silly triggered ability.",
